 :tx/rationale "Create task: C9-STEER-2v2: Full SteeringVector with context-sensitive acquisition function for read commands. PROBLEM: (1) compute_read_steering() returns Option<String> — just the question. The Steering Manifold §2 requires THREE components: concept_membership, structural_gap, question. The create path already produces all three via ObserveSteering{concept_line, gap_line, question}. The read paths only produce the question. (2) All read subcommands pass context_embedding=None, producing the same context-free question for every query. APPROACH: (A) Change compute_read_steering signature to return ObserveSteering (the same struct used by create). This satisfies INV-REFLEXIVE-007 — same type for both paths. (B) Compute concept_membership line: for list, show top 3 concepts by size with developmental stage. For search, show the concepts that matched observations belong to. For show, show the entity's concept. For recent, show the concept of the most recent observation. (C) Compute structural_gap line: the second-highest-alpha action from the acquisition function, expressed as a structural observation. (D) Wire context embeddings: run_search embeds the search pattern; run_show uses entity's embedding; run_recent uses most recent observation's embedding; run_list uses centroid of largest under-explored concept. (E) The return type ObserveSteering is already pub in kernel and exported in lib.rs — no new types needed. ACCEPTANCE: (A) compute_read_steering returns ObserveSteering. (B) All 3 fields populated for each subcommand. (C) Different search queries produce different steering vectors (context-sensitivity). (D) INV-REFLEXIVE-007: ObserveSteering is the SAME type used by create path. (E) JSON output has concept_membership + structural_gap + steering_question. DEPENDS-ON: STEER-1v2 (output templates must be in place first). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (compute_read_steering), crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs (all run_* functions)"
